name: Daron Nefcy
bio: Artist, writer, mom and creator of the show “Star vs the Forces of Evil." Currently working on something new. ❤️

bio_keywords.entity: star vs the forces of evil

social_posts.post_text: I had a lot of fun making a calendar page for this year’s @animationguild calendar! Of course my goth girl heart had to do something spooky so this is the page for October 🎃
Took this picture last October on my underwater camera 🐢

Was just visiting my favorite store @sustain_la and got this reusable cotton swab! I’m excited to try it and never buy cotton swabs again. Plastic cotton buds are one of the most problematic litter items found on beaches across the world. 1.5 billion single-use plastic cotton buds are produced each day. Many end up in our waterways and oceans.
Yay!!! I’m so excited! Just found out myself and all the directors of We the People won Emmys! Woohoo! Congrats everyone! Such a cool project. I’m so happy to be a part of it. #wethepeople #emmys2022
Drawings from the little square sketchbook

Two months ago today, my father, Jay Nefcy passed away peacefully. My dad was a big personality who had nothing but love for his family and friends. He was my biggest supporter in everything I wanted to do in my life. He was a wonderful grandpa. I miss him so much.
TBT. 10 years ago!!! Working on season one of #starvstheforcesofevil in my new office at Disney TVA
Years back I painted these Russian nesting dolls I was given as a gift and they still hang out in my house. 🪆
20 years of friendship! @carlyveronica  @heyashleyk and I met in community college while we were getting our portfolios together to apply to @calarts ! We all got in the same year. :)

Got my Emmy in the mail this week! Thank you so much @chrisnee4660 @tim_rauch @jovannananana @andradaymusic @barackobama @michelleobama @netflix and all the other director, musicians, artists and producers for letting me be part of this wonderful and very special project! #wethepeoplenetflix
New tattoo. A little 4 leaf clover by my ankle in honor of my dad. A lucky optimist from a big Irish family. I miss him a lot.🍀 thank you @tattooist_inkandbloom
TBT. Pencil drawing from my CalArts days
I was so excited to visit the @thesatanictemple in Salem! I’m a big fan of the documentary Hail Satan? If you haven’t checked out the documentary please do!
My toddler fell asleep on the plane so I got to draw for fun a little ✨
Look at this beautiful plate the incredibly talented @edjuandraws made me!!! Hand crafted and painted! ❤️❤️❤️
Actual quotes from my 2 year old 👶

Today I got to visit @atthebirdhouse. 
“The BirdHouse is a community garden in Hollywood, serving as a hub of exchange for those attracted to caring for the land and people through arts and ecology.” It’s a part of @ecorestorationcommunities who are all about restoring degraded ecosystems around the world! I’m a big fan, please check them out. They have camps and programs around the world and are working hard to help the environment. Anyone can join and help. 🐝 🌸 ❤️!!
Wow! Coolest thing I’ve ever gotten in the mail! #wethepeoplenetflix was such an honor to work on! So cool to get this letter and amazing record with all the songs from the project!

social_posts.post_text: I had such a great time at last night’s CalArts Producers’ Show! Congrats to all the hard working students. the films were wonderful ❤️

Yay! Thank you so much @turnhamator for this advanced copy of your book! National Monuments of the USA is an incredible follow up to the National Parks book Chris illustrated a few years ago! This one comes out June 13th but you and pre order on the link on his page. Really beautiful book. My son has been enjoying looking at it. ❤️
Went to @thegentlebarn for Mother’s Day! The animals were so sweet. What a lovely place!
Wow! It’s been 4 years ago today since the last episode of Star vs the Forces of Evil premiered! Where does the time go?

social_posts.post_text: Ideas for an article illustration done a couple years back.
Some drawings from the brown sketchbook ✍️
Went to help support the writers today on the picket line! Y’all keep kicking ass! And hopefully the animation guild can follow your lead next year.  #wgastrong
So happy to see my girl Star still gracing the walls of Disney TVA! 🥰

Vancouver!!!! My wonderfully talented friend @edjuandraws has been working hard on this show! It showcases work from queer printmakers and you know it’s going to be great! If you live in Vancouver or happen to be visiting please check it out! Or is it Oot? 🇨🇦!

Portland! Anyone need something really rad to do this Saturday? My super cool cousin @rachel_c_linden has been working hard on a big, public art project! The Saturday event will have really good live music, food carts + drinks, + an all women’s skate crew from NY! So cool! @Depavepdx @groundscoreassociation @mllymttrn
So sad to hear of the passing of Paul Reubens. I’ve been a huge fan ever since I was a little kid and to say he was a big influence on my art would be an understatement. Thank you @peeweeherman ❤️
Halloween 2010 or maybe 2011? Miss Yvonne and PeeWee ❤️

I wrote an essay for a book and now it’s out! The book is a collection of essays from different moms on the topic of career and the pandemic. “The COVID-19 pandemic disrupted the global world but impacted women with children and careers disproportionately. The social, familial, and professional strains of this crisis birthed with it the opportunity to reflect on the values, expectations, lifestyle, and priorities that have defined motherhood.” It’s available on Amazon.
I had a really great time today at @tentenphotosynth Kokedama workshop! I would highly recommend if you want to learn something new about plants and make some cute kokedamas to take home🪴!

Cincinnati! I’m going to have a small painting for sale in a group art show at my friend @muffinheadtv new gallery! You know it will be fun with awesome people. If I lived in Cincinnati I would be there and if you do you should be!
Water color, gold paint, markers and sharpie

Hi. I’m still here. It’s my birthday 🥳
Some very early Star drawings from 2008 or 2009

I’ve got an art show next month! I’m going to be selling paintings at Leanna Lin's Wonderland and they’ll be up in the shop later next week! Leanna Lin’s is located at- 5024 Eagle Rock Blvd. Los Angeles, CA 90041. Please join us for the opening on Saturday February 3rd from 6-9pm. Her store is super cute and the paintings will be up for awhile so please stop by anytime it’s open. And if you want to own an original painting by me now’s your chance to get some fun ones. :)
